@NODE Status_field "Status field"
After the starting routine a window appears and the program check for a
Virus. The program need therefore the origin name of the program. Please
don`t rename the program. There are 6 buttons for 6 matrix-memory-places.
Below these buttons there are the function-buttons. In the bottom of the
window there is the "Status field". The Status field shows informations
about the program.

Important: The first 2 numbers of the Status field shows the last and the
last but one marked matrix. That means:

You klick on matrix-button 3
You klick on matrix-button 5

Status field shows `35`

You klick on `*` and the program calculates matrix3 * matrix5

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
@ENDNODE

@NODE Polnish_Reverse_Notation "Polnish Reverse Notation"
You want to calculate A+B

The Addition is an operation of 2 elements:

 1. klick matrix `A` (matrix button of `A` change to marked)
 2. klick matrix `B` (matrix button of `B` change to marked)
 3. klick `+`

The solution will be stored in memory place `7`.

Operations of 2 matrices (+,-,*,...) always use the described Polnish
Reverse Notation.

Operations of 1 matrix (^,^T,DEL,...) always use the last marked matrix.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
@ENDNODE

