@NODE edit_matrix "edit matrix"
Edit the matrix elements

@ENDNODE

@NODE complex_->_real "complex -> real"
Delete the imaginary part of the marked matrix

@ENDNODE

@NODE real_->_complex "real -> complex"
Adds an imaginary part to every matrix element and set it to 0.

@ENDNODE

@NODE real_part_->_0 "real part -> 0"
Set real part of matrix to 0.

@ENDNODE

@NODE imaginary_part_->_0 "imaginary part -> 0"
Set imaginary part of matrix to 0.

@ENDNODE

@NODE matrix_->_identity_matrix_I "matrix -> identity matrix I"
If matrix is a sqaure matrix, an identity matrix will be created.

@ENDNODE

@NODE delete_all "delete all"
The matrices 1-6 will be deleted.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Option "Option"
@{" display " Link display}
@{" mode " Link mode}
@ENDNODE

@NODE display "display"
 -all matrices will be displayed

 -only the marked matrix will be displayed

@ENDNODE

@NODE mode "mode"
The values of the elements shown in the display will always be formated:

                +000.000  8 numbers wide (+10e+3 = +10 * (10*10*10))


                +000      4 numbers wide
                          0.009 is displayed as 0
                          10000 is displayed as ***

                +0        2 numbers wide
                          0.1 is displayed as  0
                          100 is displayed as  ***

@ENDNODE

