@NODE Def. "Def."
Define marked matrix. Matrix Input Window apears on screen.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Name "Name"
Define matrix-name

@ENDNODE

@NODE <-> "<->"
Change marked matrices

@ENDNODE

@NODE a*Matrix "a*Matrix"
 a * A           (a real constant)

 (a+bi) * A      (A is a complex matrix and a,b are real constants)

@ENDNODE

@NODE ^T "^T"
transpose marked matrix

@ENDNODE

@NODE ^-1 "^-1"
inverse marked matrix (must be a square matrix)

@ENDNODE

@NODE Det "Det"
calculate the determinant of the marked matrix (must be a square matrix)

@ENDNODE

@NODE Ax=B "Ax=B"
solve A * x = B

B last marked matrix
A last but one marked matrix

possibilities:

-exactly one solution
-no solution
-infinitely many solutions

@ENDNODE

@NODE +,- "+,-"
Marked matrix is +/- of the last but one marked matrix
Both matrices must the same typ

@ENDNODE

@NODE * "*"
Multiply marked matrix with the last but one marked matrix.

Remark: A*B <> B*A    (not ever, but mostly)

@ENDNODE

@NODE ^ "^"
A^a  (a is a real integer constant and a>1)

@ENDNODE

@NODE DEL "DEL"
Delete marked matrix on doubleklick

@ENDNODE

@NODE View "View"
Shows all or only the marked matrix

@ENDNODE

@NODE Stat "Stat"
Status of matrix memory places

@ENDNODE

@NODE 1-6 "1-6"
 6 matrix memory places

@ENDNODE

@NODE (7) "(7)"
Matrix memory place of the solution-matrix

@ENDNODE

@NODE (8) "(8)"
free matrix memory  @{" --> " Link -->}

@ENDNODE

@NODE --> "-->"
copy 7 to 8   @{" (8) " Link (8)}

@ENDNODE

@NODE TXT->RAM "TXT->RAM"
Copy text of window to RamDisk:

@ENDNODE

@NODE INPUT "INPUT"
Here you have to input the matrix elements.

There are 2 Modes:

In the Define mode you specify the matrix.

In the Input mode you enter the elements.


`Start` change from Define to Input mode.
`Reset` change from Input to Define mode.


@{" What? " Link What?}
@ENDNODE

@NODE What? "What?"
`OK`                    You transfer the matrix to main program

`Cursortaten`           When no field is activ (klick on title bar)
                        you move the entries with the cursor-key.
                        here you are able to see the not rounded values of
                        the elements!

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
@ENDNODE

@NODE And_now_to_something... "And now to something..."
 ...comletely different!

Hello translator!

The english version use very bad english. I hope you understand that it
is a math program and not a pic-viewer. As long as this part is in the
version of Amatrix in Aminet, every translator is welcome to translate
this doc or better the german version and the following catalog files to
good english. Please sent the translation to me and you will get a free
key-file for your job per E-Mail.

Translations to other languages are just so welcome and rewarded by a
free key-file. You have to translate the two catalog files and the
english or better the german version of the documentation.

@{" catalog1 " Link catalog1}
@{" catalog2 " Link catalog2}
@ENDNODE

